scalapack
------------------------------------------
ScaLAPACK, or Scalable LAPACK, is a library of high performance linear algebra
routines for distributed memory computers supporting MPI.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.6-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  libgfortran5-9.3.0-2
  liblapack-devel-3.9.0-2
  liblapack0-3.9.0-2
  libopenblas-0.3.10-1
  libopenmpi-devel-3.1.6-1
  libopenmpi40-3.1.6-1
  libscalapack-devel-2.1.0-1bl1
  libscalapack0-2.1.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-fortran-9.3.0-2
  ninja-1.10.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Reference-ScaLAPACK/scalapack

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Reference-ScaLAPACK/scalapack/archive/v2.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack scalapack-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./scalapack-2.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/scalapack-2.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/scalapack-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscalapack0-2.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscalapack-devel-2.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(scalapack)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/scalapack.README
  /usr/share/doc/scalapack/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/scalapack/README

(libscalapack0)
  /usr/bin/cygscalapack-0.dll

(libscalapack-devel)
  /usr/include/blacs/Bconfig.h
  /usr/include/blacs/Bdef.h
  /usr/include/pblas/PBblacs.h
  /usr/include/pblas/PBblas.h
  /usr/include/pblas/PBpblas.h
  /usr/include/pblas/PBtools.h
  /usr/include/pblas/pblas.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/scalapack-2.1.0/scalapack-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/scalapack-2.1.0/scalapack-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/scalapack-2.1.0/scalapack-targets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/scalapack-2.1.0/scalapack-targets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libscalapack.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/scalapack.pc

